data.description: Built circa 1888 this beautiful Queen Anne Victorian maintains a lot of original character. It has 3 fireplaces, 3 pocket doors, hardwood floors, original trim around the windows and doors, gingerbread exterior trim, a walk up attic, butler's pantry and more. The home has a 2nd story laundry room and master bath suite with tub and separate shower. The walk up attic could be finished for addtional space. Carport behind home for off street parking.
